The paper deals with the problem of recovering a time sequence of sparse vectors corrupted by structured noise, which is a common problem in signal processing and information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a novel solution approach that involves compressive sensing and principal component analysis, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and data analysis. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.SP (Signal Processing), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves mathematical analysis and optimization, which are common in numerical analysis and scientific computing. Therefore, cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is also a likely sub-category.
